description:
Manual games allow you to set custom check locations and custom item names that will be rolled into a multiworld.
This allows any variety of game -- PC, console, board games, Microsoft Word memes... really anything -- to be part of a multiworld randomizer.
The key component to including these games is some level of manual restriction. Since the items are not actually withheld from the player,
the player must manually refrain from using these gathered items until the tracker shows that they have been acquired or sent.

Sudoku_1.0.0.description:
First big release of the Sudoku manual.

Full readme is [HERE](https://github.com/axxroytovu/archipelago_manuals/blob/2e01e04141e1418c3fca68b484cccf56eee3cf83/Sudoku/README.md)

New in this version:
- Total of 300+ puzzles
- Working expected game length in hours
- Refactored regions to remove unnecessary keys in shorter games
- Extra victory keys now input as percent added, not total percent
Sudoku_1.0.0.title: Sudoku - 1.0.0

Sudoku_1.1.0.description:
Sudoku major update:
- Requires generating on Archipelago 0.4.4. To generate on version 0.4.3, please use release [1.0.0](https://github.com/axxroytovu/archipelago_manuals/releases/tag/Sudoku_1.0.0)
- Nearly 1100 puzzles!
- Positional category is split into Positional (extra regions, irregular, anti-king) and Comparison (thermo, consecutive, skyscraper)

Readme is available [here](https://github.com/axxroytovu/archipelago_manuals/blob/232018922fb0a961cb5e68900167c2c9a69342d6/Sudoku/README.md)
